         <p>William Glover Fletcher Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_7a45923a9c07119c4783ae63b98078bb">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>William Glover Fletcher received a bachelor of arts degree from Clark University in 1936. He went to Yale for graduate work, writing a Ph.D. Dissertation entitled, Canal Site Diplomacy: A Study in American Political Geography. He received the Ph.D. in 1940, but stayed at Yale until 1943 as an instructor in international relations and as a fellow of Pierson College. He died in 1968.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_916f06d3bbb994667b8a4e80ce0870e6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Correspondence and research material on the Panama Canal gathered by William Glover Fletcher presumably in connection with his Ph.D. dissertation: Canal Site Diplomacy: A Study in American Political Geography (Yale University, 1940). His single correspondent is Philippe Bunau-Varilla, whose study on the founding of Panama is also included in the papers.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
